{
  "texts": [
    "By identifying and summarizing such challenges and opportunities, we aim to stimulate further research on devices, circuits, and systems for the silicon photonics ecosystem.",
    "Figure 1 maps the evolution of silicon photonics 1, 2.",
    "Silicon-based photonic integrated circuits (PICs) were introduced in 1985 3 and low-loss waveguides in a thick silicon on insulator (SOI) process demonstrated in 1991-92 4, 5.",
    "Various optical devices were next demonstrated 6, and soon, silicon photonics was in the small-scale integration (SSI) erawith 1-to-10 components on a PIC.",
    "They included demonstrations of high-speed pn junction modulators [7] [8] [9] and photodetectors (PDs) [10] [11] [12] [13], as well as heterogeneous integration of a III-V laser to a silicon PIC 14."
  ]
}